Proverbs 2-11 <t><f>ⓝ</f> discretion will <f>ⓞ</f>watch over you, </t><t>understanding will guard you,</t>
Proverbs 2-12 <t>delivering you from the way of evil, </t><t>from men of perverted speech,</t>
Proverbs 2-13 <t>who forsake the paths of uprightness </t><t>to <f>ⓟ</f>walk in the ways of darkness,</t>
